cs.CL, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.NE, cs.IR 

This paper focuses on using neural network models to identify event temporal status by extracting dependency chains containing context events. This task involves natural language processing and machine learning, which are covered by the sub-categories of computational linguistics (cs.CL), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), and machine learning (cs.LG). Additionally, the use of neural network models falls under the sub-category of neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE). Finally, the task of identifying event temporal status can also be considered a form of information retrieval (cs.IR).
